's  East Lynne (  1861 ) and  Edna Lyall's  In the Golden Days (  1885 ). Modern use may well have been influenced also by the common Irish surname derived from the medieval Norman male name.  See also  Joss ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":15,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Joyce Waldeboeff was born about 1300, in Lechlade-On-Thames, Gloucestershire, England, her father, Philip Walbeoffe, was 23 and her mother, Jane Solers, was 29. She had at least 1 son with Roger Vaughan. She died about 1320, in her hometown, at the age of 22."},"et":{"about 1300–about 1320":"umbes 1300–umbes 1320","1300–1320":"1300–1320","1302–1335":"1302–1335","1290–1320":"1290–1320","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1278–1335":"1278–1335","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1302":"1302","1378":"1378","1278":"1278","1300":"1300","1320":"1320","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1272":"1272","about 1320":"umbes 1320","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England":"Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England","Lechlade, Gloucestershire, England":"Lechlade-On-Thames, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1300–about 1320":"noin 1300–noin 1320","1300–1320":"1300–1320","1302–1335":"1302–1335","1290–1320":"1290–1320","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1278–1335":"1278–1335","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1302":"1302","1378":"1378","1278":"1278","1300":"1300","1320":"1320","about 1300":"noin 1300","1272":"1272","about 1320":"noin 1320","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England":"Bredwardine, Herefordshire, England","Lechlade, Gloucestershire, England":"Lechlade-On-Thames, G